3) Write a program to get the tuple elements in a single line separated by spaces and print the number of elements in the given tuple.
Sample Input:
10 20 30
...
ans
input_string = input("Enter the tuple elements separated by spaces: ")
tuple_elements = tuple(map(int, input_string.split()))
print("Tuple:", tuple_elements)
print("Number of elements in the tuple:", len(tuple_elements))
output:
Enter the tuple elements separated by spaces: 15
Tuple: (15,)
Number of elements in the tuple: 1
